  "instructions": [
    "In a mortar and pestle, grind cumin, coriander, cardamom, cinnamon, dried mint, and dried rosemary into a fine powder.",
    "Cut the lamb shoulder into 2 cm cubes and season with salt, pepper, and the ground spice mix.",
    "Heat the cedar plank over medium heat until it starts to smoke slightly, then add olive oil and brown the lamb cubes on all sides.",
    "Transfer the browned lamb to a large pot and sauté the chopped onion and minced garlic until translucent.",
    "Add the black treacle, dried apricots, dates, figs, and prunes to the pot, stirring to coat the ingredients.",
    "Pour in the vegetable stock, add bay leaves, and bring the mixture to a gentle simmer, then reduce heat and cover.",
    "Cook the stew on low heat for 90 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the lamb is tender and the flavors have melded.",
    "Remove the cedar plank, discard the bay leaves, and serve the stew hot, garnished with fresh cilantro if desired."
  ],
